type PolicyDecision =
  | { kind: 'allow';   rule?: string }
  | { kind: 'deny';    rule: string; reason: string }
  | { kind: 'require'; rule: string; approver: 'human_approver'; ttlMs: number }

Land in policy.ts alongside the existing PolicyRule schema. This is the output contract; do not confuse with PolicyRule.effect (auto_approve|deny|require_approval), which is the input. No 'prompt' variant — that was never in the frozen doc.

Acceptance:
- PolicyDecision exported from policy.ts
- Type-level tests (expect-type or similar) verify all three kinds construct cleanly
- No runtime validation (decisions are produced by evaluate(), not parsed from untrusted input)"}

